A still stronger evidence of this is to be found in the ancient names of persons. There would seem to be no safer method of determining the ancient pronunciation of letters than by a recurrence to the proper names in which they are to be found. Names alter little, if at all, for centuries. They are in constant use, and handed down in hundreds and thousands of families from one to another genera- tion.
